properties.sfomuseum:description: Airmail flight cover, part of International Tributes to the History of Flight series by the Postal Commemorative Society; white envelope with full color illustration cachet and inset stamp commemorating first manned orbit of the moon on December 21, 1968, at Cape Canaveral, Florida, U.S.A., by Colonel Frank Borman, Captain James Lovell, Jr., and Major William Anders with Apollo 8 spacecraft; cancellation stamp dated December 21, 1983 in Cape Canaveral; includes information on reverse.
